Sentencas: Complex oxides Nd1.6Ca0.4Ni1-yCuyO4+delta (y = 0.0-0.4) have been prepared by a pyrolysis of glycerol-nitrate compositions.
Titulo: Crystal structure and functional properties of Nd1.6Ca0.4Ni1-yCuyO4+δ as prospective cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: According to the X-ray diffraction analysis, the materials are single-phase up to y = 0.3 and crystallize in an orthorhombic structure (Bmab) at room temperature.
Titulo: Crystal structure and functional properties of Nd1.6Ca0.4Ni1-yCuyO4+δ as prospective cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: High-temperature studies assert that they all undergo a phase transition from orthorhombic to tetragonal (I4/ mmm) structure in a range of 300-400 degrees C. With Cu doping, the over-stoichiometric oxygen content delta decreases from 0.07 (y = 0.0) down to 0.00 (y = 0.3).
Titulo: Crystal structure and functional properties of Nd1.6Ca0.4Ni1-yCuyO4+δ as prospective cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The studies on the compact samples reveal the maximum value of total conductivity (165 S cm(-1) at 420 degrees C) and the minimum value of the linear coefficient of thermal expansion (11.9.10(-6) K-1 in a range of 400-1000 degrees C in air) at y = 0.2.
Titulo: Crystal structure and functional properties of Nd1.6Ca0.4Ni1-yCuyO4+δ as prospective cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Chemical compatibility of the Nd1.6Ca0.4Ni1-yCuyO4-delta (y = 0.0, 0.2) oxides with oxygen- and proton conducting electrolytes (Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95, Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 and BaCe0.5Zr0.3Y0.1Yb0.1O3-delta) up to a temperature of 1100 degrees C is demonstrated.
Titulo: Crystal structure and functional properties of Nd1.6Ca0.4Ni1-yCuyO4+δ as prospective cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
